 No, it's not.

00:02:18.440 --> 00:02:21.760
 So, why don't you tell us that story? Because I think pivot stores are always

00:02:21.760 --> 00:02:26.120
 interesting because so many companies end up doing things that are radically different

00:02:26.120 --> 00:02:27.320
 than where they started.

00:02:27.320 --> 00:02:32.760
 Yeah. So, it's kind of a pivot story. It's kind of not really a pivot story. So,

00:02:32.760 --> 00:02:37.640
 my co-founder and I, we have been entrepreneurs for over a dozen years working together.

00:02:37.640 --> 00:02:42.080
 Our backgrounds were in large software development. I was at Microsoft and he was

00:02:42.080 --> 00:02:49.920
 at Hewlett Packard. And we left our jobs to start building websites, actually.

00:02:49.920 --> 00:02:56.080
 So, our initial company together was building a site that aggregated

00:02:56.080 --> 00:03:00.800
 restaurant menus and put those online, learned a lot about sort of just building

